Below is an example demonstrating how to evolve the CardMetadata struct to include more complex data structures (e.g., separate structs for attacks, weaknesses/resistances, or abilities). Notice that struct and array usage in Solidity can significantly increase gas costs for storage and minting, so you should carefully consider off-chain storage if the dataset is large.

